answerText: David Hilbert's problems for the 20th century [accept Hilbert spaces][10] The first of Hilbert's problems is this conjecture, which was shown to be undecidable under the ZFC axioms. It asserts that there exists no set with cardinality between that of the natural numbers and the real numbers.
